So....I found this story I wrote in like....the 5th grade....it is really really really bad.....wanna read?


I pulled the car to a stop on the old dirt road, shuting off the engine and sitting there for a moment. I stared at the sight in front of me, taking it in. It has been a long time. Opening the door I step out of the car, my eyes searching the ground before it. After a moment, I see it. A faint reminence of a trail that used to be. I begin my journy on it, my tired and worn body wandering the slim path. My eyes travel the sites in front of me, taking me back to remember him. I remember that first day I saw him sleeping in my hide away.  I watched him sleep and fell in love with his breathing. He woke after hours, and I had no choice but to love the rest of him as well.  Every day I would rush to meet him here, and every day found him asleep. Every day I would watch him and fall in love with his breathing, and every day he would wake, and I would fall in love with the rest of him. I remember all of this as I step into my clearing, our clearing.  I also remember the day he went away, dressed so handsome in his uniform. He promised to meet me here again, when he returned, and take me away. It's been so long..I waited and grew old. It's time for him to come now, I know it is. I lay down in the grass, where I would always find him, letting my eyes close as I wait. I hear his breathing and know he is there. My eyes open and there he is, so handsome in his uniform. He takes my hand and we fade away...I'm with my love at last...

Yami, we still have FOUR years until we can be together...(and, I doubt we will see each other in between...unless I decide to take a roadtrip one weekend..O.o)..but, I love you...and if you love me even half of what you say you do, then....it will be alright, and we will make it...It will be hard of course...but..we will get through...four years isn't THAT long....

Yeah, my entry WAS emotion...that was the point, to get what I felt off my chest..thats the whole point of a journal...If you don't like it, the don't read it...-Is by no means pointing out one person...this goes to everyone- It is my journal, and it will say what I think and what I feel and what is going through MY head...you..are just along for the ride I guess....and..there are exits on everyside of you...feel free to leave at anytime. Go ahead and post and try to change my opinoin on things...but, it doesn't mean it will work...I put what I have learned through my life...and if I learn different...and not just through someone elses opinion..I will be more than happy to change the way I think...as most of you would..and again...I apologize to the very very very very few girls who have shown me that they arn't like the rest. I still prefer guys, that is me.
